item.title: Midterm 1: Cheat Sheet
item.description: \(\) Asymptotic Bound # Notation Meaning Definition $$\mathcal O(\cdot)$$ $$\le$$ $$\lim_{n \to \infty} \dfrac{f(n)}{g(n)} < \infty$$ $$\Theta (\cdot)$$ $$=$$ $$\lim_{n \to \infty} \dfrac{f(n)}{g(n)} = c$$ $$\Omega(\cdot)$$ $$\ge$$ $$\lim_{n \to \infty} \dfrac{f(n)}{g(n)}> 0$$ $$\begin{aligned} c &< \log^\star n \\ &< \log n \\ &< n^{1/3}\\ &< n^{1/2} = \sqrt n\\ &< 2^{\log{n}} = n\\ &< n \log (n) = \log(n!) \\ &< n^3\\ &< 2^{\sqrt{n}}\\ &< 2^n\\ &< 3^n\\ &< n!
